data.description: The one you've been waiting on! Well kept, and located on a beautiful lot desirable Crowfield Plantation! Featuring a traditional, yet open floor plan, you will appreciate your formal and everyday living spaces. A oversized driveway, and full front porch welcomes you at arrival. Make your way inside to find a vaulted 2 story foyer, the formal dining room to the right and then a flex space to the left. This space would make a great home office, play room, or additional living room. Accessible from the dining room is the kitchen, downstairs powder room, and garage. The kitchen and great room are situated on the rear of the home and oveWood cabinets, with custom wood island, black stainless appliances, and double pantries complete the kitchen. A huge plus is that all kitchen appliances to include the refrigerator along with the washer and dryer convey with the home at no additional cost to the buyer! A spacious living room is open to the kitchen and is accented by a white/washed gas fireplace! Pergo laminate flooring, crown molding, smooth ceilings, and upgraded lighting runs through most of the downstairs. Make your way to the 2nd floor where all 3 bedrooms are located. Two secondary bedrooms have nice size closets and share a full bathroom. The primary suite is oversized and has a vaulted ceiling, huge walk-in closet, and private en-suite with soaking tub, separate shower, private toiletry room, and ceramic tile flooring. All bathroom mirrors have built-in storage behind them in case you need extra space for toiletries. Outside you will enjoy a spacious fenced backyard with plush lawn and 2 patios. This home has been well taken care of and is ready for it's new owner. Homeowners will enjoy being able to use the neighborhood pool, walking trails, play park, and tennis courts. Golf Memberships are available for an additional fee. Buyers to verify all information they deem as important.
